description:
6pm to 6am curfew set by government; 

Adapted on March 30 to 2pm to 7am and work hours limited from 9.00-12.00

Update: Ended on April 20, 2020 due to qualitative change in the policy (target population now includes everyone except fuel drivers. On April 20, it was announced by the Fuel Crisis Committee that drivers for fuel distribution centers and drivers of trucks delivering LPG bottled gas cylinders will be exempted from the curfew. UPDATE: Qualitative change policy due to change in target pop. Therefore this policy will be ended.
